Lalisa Manoban (ลลิษา มโนบาล)

description.plain:
Born in Bangkok, Thailand as Pranpriya Manobal on March 27, 1997, Lalisa Manobal (ลลิษา มโนบาล) is a member of South Korean girl group BLACKPINK, which was formed by YG Entertainment in 2016.

She grew up in the Buriram Province and was raised by her mother and stepfather. During her childhood, she was a member of a Thai dance group titled We Zaa Cool along with BamBam of GOT7 and Ten of NCT 127.

In 2010, she auditioned for YG Entertainment in Thailand because she wanted to become an idol in South Korea. She later visited a fortune-teller with her mom and they told her to change her name to Lalisa, which means “one who is praised.” A week later, Lisa got the call and became a YG trainee in April 2011, making her the first international trainee of the company.

She was revealed to the public a year later through a dance cover of Chris Brown’s “Turn Up The Music.” The video was uploaded to YG’s YouTube channel with the title Who’s That Girl?, which was the catchphrase used for all the teasers of YG’s new girl group members. Its debut was delayed several years until June 8, 2016, when Lisa was confirmed as the second member of BLACKPINK.

On September 10, 2021, Lisa made her solo debut with the release of her self-titled single album, LALISA. The title track “LALISA” broke two Guinness world records with its music video, which got 73,6 million views the day of release. The first record was for the most-viewed YouTube music video in 24 hours and the second record was for the most-viewed YouTube music video in 24 hours by a solo K-pop artist. Besides that, both tracks in the single album made it to the Billboard Hot 100, Billboard Global 200 and Global Excl. U.S. charts.

A month after LALISA, she continued with her solo career and collaborated with French producer DJ Snake on “SG” with American-rapper Megan Thee Stallion and Puerto-Rican singer Ozuna.

songs.title: MONEY

description.plain:
The electronic-pop “MONEY” is the second track on the singer’s solo debut album, LALISA. The aftermentioned style is mixed with hip-pop and a soft ballad pop during the pre-chorus. The outro also showcases a trap side to the song making it stand out. The song involves YG producer, Teddy Park’s special style consisting of a moody pre-chorus building up into a catchy surprising chorus.

Lyrically, the song is about LISA’s a wealth and her affluent day-to-day life through her un-destroyable fans and support. The singer also takes time to brag about her skyrocketing fame as a member of BLACKPINK and her record-breaking solo releases.

The song was also promoted with a TikTok challenge called LISA ‘MONEY’ dance challenge. The challenge used the official choreography of the chorus and went viral.

songs.title: LALISA

description.plain:
On “LALISA,” BLACKPINK’s LISA confidently kicks off her solo career. The song marks her first solo release and is the leading track off her debut album, LALISA, named after her real name—Lalisa Manoban.

The track has an upbeat electronic-pop instrumental that fits LISA’s vocals and matches the visuals of the music video. Lyrically, the song exhibits her attitude, how she owns the vibe, and is her real self, LALISA.

The music video emphasizes the song’s main theme through choreography referring to the first letters of her name “LA,” showed as hand symbols. In another scene, LISA displays her Thai culture with The Great Crown of Victory. The crown represents the concept of divine monarchy, where the tall spire is a symbol of authority and the right to rule over their subjects. She’s also wearing clothes made by Thai designer, Polpat Asavaprapha of ASAVA, inspired by the traditional Thai Sabai top and a sarong wrap skirt. In addition, LISA is wearing an ear cuff inspired by Sangwan, a ceremonial necklace that symbolizes wealth and fortune, as well as bringing the aura of Thai culture by using gardenia flowers.

Besides LISA’s Thai clothing, the golden set in the music video is a recreation of the Phanom Rung Historical Park in Buriram Province, Thailand—LISA’s hometown.

The song was promoted via multiple teasers on LISA’s own social media account, as well as BLACKPINK’s, and came along with the “LALISA” YouTube dance challenge.

songs.title: SAY SO

description.plain:
“Say So” is Lisa’s cover of Doja Cat’s hit, performed during BLACKPINK’s virtual concert THE SHOW on January 31, 2021.

Lisa co-wrote and co-composed a new rap verse for the cover with Danny Chung. She also designed the choreography and stage concept for the live performance.
